snippet.textDisplay:
Love how in The Sims your Sim dies of starvation just because you didn't control them. They had a functioning kitchen. They had their own house. Living alone. Yet they never on their own accord left the house to talk to people, and when they for once left the house, they kinda liked it so much they just didn't come back to the house in days, living in discomfort next to a pond for a day, until coming back to the house.
That's how the A.I works.
